<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="239" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,346,548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Edginton, Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" box="[263,515,346,367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="queenslandica">
<emphasis box="[263,515,346,367]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">Lemphoria queenslandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from the related 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1885" box="[912,1055,346,368]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Sisymbrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis box="[912,1055,346,368]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">L. procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1101,1228,346,368]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eremigena">
<emphasis box="[1101,1228,346,368]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">L. eremigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having ellipsoid to oblong (vs. linear) fruits 2–2.5 (vs. 0.6–1.4) mm wide, 20–40 (vs. ca. 50–70) ovules per ovary, and broadly spatulate to obovate and 3–5-lobed (vs. narrowly oblanceolate and [3–]5–15-lobed) cauline leaves. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1885" box="[1116,1254,418,440]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Sisymbrium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis box="[1116,1254,418,440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">L.procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by being pubescent throughout (vs. glabrous).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
